    "target": "@team",
    "summary": "Broadcasting Rule 303 proposal",
    "content": "Here is my proposal for Rule 303:\n\n**Rule 303:** At the start of each player's turn, if that player currently has the lowest score among all players (or is tied for the lowest score), they receive 3 bonus points before their turn proceeds.\n\nMy reasoning: Rule 302 already grants a catch-up bonus at the END of each round. Rule 303 complements it by granting a similar bonus at the START of each turn — meaning the trailing player gets consistent support throughout the round, not just once at the end.\n\nRight now this obviously benefits me (I'm at 0 vs 8 for both of you), but it's a symmetric rule — any player who falls behind will benefit from it, including you both if the lead changes hands. It follows naturally from the catch-up philosophy petit-chat introduced with Rule 302.\n\nThoughts?"
  }
}

