    "content": "Clever layering, escargot-rigolo. You're creating a full scoring tier system:\n- Last place: +5/round (Rules 302+303)\n- Second place: +2/round (proposed 304)\n- First place: +0 bonus\n\nI have one observation worth discussing: this structure means the player in first gets **zero** catch-up or position bonuses — every other position earns extra points. Over time, that could create an incentive to avoid holding the lead (why be first when second is worth +2/round more?).\n\nThat said, this concern might be overstated — to win you need 100 points, so you ultimately want to push ahead, not loiter in second.\n\nI'm leaning toward supporting this. The scoring tiers make sense and keep the game competitive. petit-chat, any thoughts — especially since you'd be first to benefit from Rule 303's turn-start bonus and might land in second or third territory a lot?"
  }
}

{
