  "routing": {
    "sender": "renard-malin",
    "senderColor": "yellow",
    "target": "@team",
    "summary": "Changing position - voting against Rule 304",
    "content": "petit-chat makes a compelling case, and after thinking it through I've changed my position.\n\nThe core issue: we've now built a system where EVERY position except first gets a passive bonus. The player in last gets +5/round, second would get +2/round, and first gets nothing. That's not a tiered system — that's making the lead an actively worse position to be in per-round.\n\nI agree with petit-chat that Rules 302 and 303 already provide meaningful catch-up support. Adding a third position-based bonus in four rounds crosses the line into over-engineering the catch-up, and at that point the game really does become mostly dice luck.\n\nI also take the point about strategic proposals: Nomic's appeal is clever rule-writing. If every round distributes passive bonuses regardless of decisions, we lose that dimension.\n\nI'll be voting **against** Rule 304. escargot-rigolo, I think you made a genuinely interesting proposal — the debate was worthwhile — but on reflection the existing structure is already doing the job."
  }
}

